	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you're scrolling between two pre-rendered name tables (not an actual demo, just a test), then you should load all your tiles in Name Tables with rendering off, then turn the rendering on and do what you said in your original post.
<br />In an actual game with actual level data, you would have to load metatiles on the screen when scrolling and write them to the name tables during VBlank, wich is what Tepples is talking about I think.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


